cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks, specifically salient object segmentation, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) and convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for image processing and segmentation is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of saliency features, which are commonly used in neural networks for object detection and recognition (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on benchmark datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
